ARPB_TRANSACTIONS.name: ARPB_TRANSACTIONS
ARPB_TRANSACTIONS.description: This table contains information about professional billing transactions.

columns.name: TX_ID
columns.description: A transaction's unique internal identification number. A patient's record can include charges, payments, or adjustments and the patient's account balance will reflect these transactions.

columns.name: POST_DATE
columns.description: The date when a transaction is entered into the billing system.  This differs from the service date, which is the date when the service was performed.

columns.name: SERVICE_DATE
columns.description: The date a medical service is performed.

columns.name: TX_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The type of this transaction: Charge, payment or adjustment.

columns.name: ACCOUNT_ID
columns.description: The internal ID of the record that maintains the patient's transactions. A patient may use more than one account and an account may contain more than one patient.

columns.name: DEBIT_CREDIT_FLAG_NAME
columns.description: This column contains a 1 if the transaction is a debit and a -1 if the transaction is a credit. A charge is always a debit, a payment is always a credit, and an adjustment can be either a debit or a credit.

columns.name: SERV_PROVIDER_ID
columns.description: The internal identifier of the provider who performed the medical services on the patient.

columns.name: BILLING_PROV_ID
columns.description: The billing provider associated with the transaction.

columns.name: DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.description: The department ID of the department associated with the transaction.

columns.name: POS_ID
columns.description: The place of service ID of the place of service associated with the transaction

columns.name: LOC_ID
columns.description: The location ID of the location associated with the transaction.

columns.name: SERVICE_AREA_ID
columns.description: The service area ID of the service area associated with the transaction.

columns.name: MODIFIER_ONE
columns.description: The first procedure modifier associated with this transaction. This is the external modifier, as it would be printed on the claim.

columns.name: PRIMARY_DX_ID
columns.description: The primary diagnosis ID associated with the transaction.

columns.name: DX_TWO_ID
columns.description: The second diagnosis ID associated with the transaction.

columns.name: DX_THREE_ID
columns.description: The third diagnosis ID associated with the transaction.

columns.name: DX_FOUR_ID
columns.description: The fourth diagnosis ID associated with the transaction.

columns.name: PROCEDURE_QUANTITY
columns.description: The quantity as entered in Charge Entry for the procedure of this transaction (TX_ID). If the row has a DETAIL_TYPE value of 10-13, this column displays a negative value. If the row has a DETAIL_TYPE value of 20-33, 43-45, 50, or 51, this column displays a zero.

columns.name: AMOUNT
columns.description: The original amount of this transaction.

columns.name: OUTSTANDING_AMT
columns.description: The outstanding amount of the transaction.

columns.name: INSURANCE_AMT
columns.description: The insurance portion of the transaction.

columns.name: PATIENT_AMT
columns.description: The patient or self-pay portion of the transaction.

columns.name: VOID_DATE
columns.description: If this transaction is voided, this column will have the date in which this transaction is voided.

columns.name: LAST_ACTION_DATE
columns.description: This column contains the most recent date when an action is performed on this transaction.

columns.name: PROV_SPECIALTY_C_NAME
columns.description: This column contains the provider specialty of the provider associated with the transaction. The procedure category of the charge on the transaction may affect what specialty is recorded here and in the "Encounter Specialty" displayed in Hyperspace.

columns.name: PROC_ID
columns.description: The Procedure ID of the procedure associated with the transaction.

columns.name: TOTAL_MATCH_AMT
columns.description: This column contains the total amount matched to the transaction, including adjustments.

columns.name: TOTAL_MTCH_INS_AMT
columns.description: This column contains the total insurance amount matched to the transaction, including adjustments.

columns.name: TOTAL_MTCH_ADJ
columns.description: This column contains the total adjustment amount matched to the transaction.

columns.name: TOTAL_MTCH_INS_ADJ
columns.description: This column contains the total insurance adjustment amount matched to the transaction.

columns.name: REPOST_ETR_ID
columns.description: This is the repost source transaction.

columns.name: REPOST_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The repost type category ID for the transaction.

columns.name: ENC_FORM_NUM
columns.description: The encounter form number corresponding to the charge transaction. If you are not using encounter forms, a negative number is stored in this item.

columns.name: BEN_SELF_PAY_AMT
columns.description: Stores the adjudicated self-pay amount calculated by the benefits engine

columns.name: BEN_ADJ_COPAY_AMT
columns.description: Stores the copay part of the adjudicated self-pay amount calculated by the benefits engine

columns.name: VISIT_NUMBER
columns.description: This item stores the visit number for this transaction.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_EPM_ID
columns.description: This item stores the original payor (EPM) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_FC_C_NAME
columns.description: This item stores the original financial class for this transaction.
entries: Sent to Consolidated Self-Pay Service Area

columns.name: ORIGINAL_CVG_ID
columns.description: This item stores the original coverage (CVG) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: PAYOR_ID
columns.description: This item stores the current payor (EPM) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: COVERAGE_ID
columns.description: This item stores the current coverage (CVG) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: ASGN_YN
columns.description: This item stores the assignment flag for a coverage.  This item is set to Yes if the charge is currently assigned to the payor in the PAYOR_ID column.

columns.name: FACILITY_ID
columns.description: This item stores the facility (EAF) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: PAYMENT_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description: This item stores the payment source for credit transactions. This is a list of possible sources including Cash, Check, Credit Card, etc.

columns.name: USER_ID
columns.description: This item stores the user who posted the transaction.

columns.name: USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: NOT_BILL_INS_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the transaction is marked for do not bill insurance.

columns.name: CHG_ROUTER_SRC_ID
columns.description: This item stores the universal charge line (UCL) ID for this transaction.

columns.name: BILL_AREA_ID
columns.description: Networked to BIL: the Bill Area for this transaction.

columns.name: BILL_AREA_ID_BILL_AREA_NAME
columns.description: The record name of this bill area, financial subdivision, or financial division.

columns.name: CREDIT_SRC_MODULE_C_NAME
columns.description: The module that creates a payment or credit adjustment

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: The date that this row was last updated.

columns.name: CLAIM_DATE
columns.description: The most recent date that this transaction has been on an accepted claim run.

columns.name: IPP_INV_NUMBER
columns.description: This item stores the original invoice number that user posts to in GUI payment posting or remittance.

columns.name: IPP_INV_ID
columns.description: This item stores the original invoice ID that user posts to in�graphical user interface�(GUI) payment posting or remittance.

columns.name: EB_PMT_TOTAL_AMT
columns.description: Displays the enterprise payment total amount.

columns.name: VST_DO_NOT_BIL_I_YN
columns.description: This item indicates whether the visit has been marked as do not bill insurance.

columns.name: TX_ENTERED_INSTANT_DTTM
columns.description: The transaction entered instant (date and time in UTC) for manually posted payments. The transaction filing instant (date and time in UTC) for electronically posted payments.

columns.name: CVG_PLAN_ON_PMT_ID
columns.description: This column contains the coverage plan associated with the invoice number stamped on an insurance payment or credit adjustment.

columns.name: STMT_HOLD_DT
columns.description: The most recent date on which the transaction was held from the Professional Billing statement processing.

columns.name: STMT_HOLD_REASON_C_NAME
columns.description: The reason why the transaction was held in PB statement processing.
entries: Minimum guarantor account balance not met
Credit balance on the guarantor account
Guarantor account already on another run
Guarantor account status not to bill
Minimum days between two statements not met
Guarantor address has no ZIP code
Charge Homing is turned on and guarantor account is not in its home
No professional balance and no hospital account to bill
Guarantor account has a hospital account with a self-pay payment/adjustment posted today
Guarantor account has a hospital account on payment plan that did not qualify
Cannot demand if form requires importing images
Statement already processed this month for payment plan
SmartText and Classic forms cannot be included in the same run
Cannot send tickler to guarantor for paperless bill
Minimum days between guarantor detail bill and statement not met
Payment plan already paid for this month
Guarantor has a balance notification scheduled or recently sent
Payment plan is currently deferred, and guarantor has only plan balances
Guarantor billing status not to bill
Guarantor does not have new activity
Guarantor does not have transactions to bill
Guarantor special billing status set to hold statements
Cannot send another statement before processing auto pay from the last statement
Client next statement date is not before or equal to end batch date

columns.name: REPOST_REASON_C_NAME
columns.description: If this transaction was reposted from another, this contains the category value of the reason the transaction was reposted.

columns.name: OUTST_CLM_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: The status of an outstanding claim that is attached to a transaction.

columns.name: POS_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Place of service type for a charge transaction.
entries: Intermediate Care Facility/ Individuals with Intellectual Disabilities
Telehealth - Provided Other than in Patient's Home

columns.name: INACTIVE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: This column returns the type of an inactive transaction.  Inactive transactions are those involved in a void or reversal. This item subcategorizes the transaction's role in the void or reversal. This will be for both the actual voided/reversed credit and the associated negation payment or debit adjustment.
entries: Debit Adjustment Used to Reverse Credit
$0 Debit Adjustment Used in Reversal By Negation

columns.name: VOIDED_INS_AMT
columns.description: The total amount owed from insurance at the time a charge was voided. This includes previously applied payments and adjustments.

columns.name: PROV_NETWORK_STAT_C_NAME
columns.description: Basic indicator of whether a provider was in or out of network on the service date of a transaction

columns.name: NETWORK_LEVEL_C_NAME
columns.description: The provider's level of network involvement category ID for the transaction.

columns.name: ADJUSTMENT_CAT_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores the adjustment category of the associated adjustment code when the credit adjustment is posted.

columns.name: WRITE_OFF_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: The reason a credit adjustment was posted. This is determined programmatically when possible (e.g. contractual adjustments, self-pay discounts). Otherwise, this is the write-off reason associated with the adjustment category for this adjustment.

columns.name: MANUAL_PRICE_OVRIDE_YN
columns.description: Permanent transaction indicator used during repost/correct/retro to determine if the charge's price was originally overridden.

columns.name: IS_PRE_SERVICE_PMT_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether or not this is a pre-service payment, such as a co-pay. This item is only populated for self-pay payments. A payment is considered pre-service if it is a visit pre-pay or co-pay payment (such as during check-in).

columns.name: FIRST_ETR_TX_ID
columns.description: Stores the transaction ID of the first transaction in a chain of transactions. Note that this chain will include transactions from both Hospital Billing and Professional Billing, so this item will return the very first transaction. For a given transaction, either column ARPB_TRANSACTIONS2.FIRST_HTR_ID, or column ARPB_TRANSACTIONS2.FIRST_ETR_ID will be populated. This is different from column ARPB_TRANSACTIONS2.FIRST_TX_ID, which only chains back to the point that the transaction was transferred from Hospital Billing.

columns.name: POSTING_DEPARTMENT_ID
columns.description: The department where the transaction was posted.

columns.name: EXP_REIMB_SRC_C_NAME
columns.description: The item stores how the reimbursement amount was calculated for the charge.

columns.name: STMT_HOLD_RSN_TEXT
columns.description: The free text information related to the reason why the transaction was held in Professional Billing statement processing.

columns.name: EB_PMT_HTT_ID
columns.description: The Enterprise payment hospital temporary transaction ID.

columns.name: PRIM_TIMELY_FILE_DEADLINE_DATE
columns.description: The primary timely filing deadline date.

columns.name: PAT_PMT_COLL_WKFL_C_NAME
columns.description: This column contains the workflow category ID performed to collect a patient payment from the point of view of the user. For example, MyChart eCheck-in vs. MyChart One-Touch.

columns.name: EB_TX_SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description: This column stores the enterprise posting module for the transaction. This is calculated based on the professional billing transaction source for the transaction.

columns.name: ORIGINATING_TAR_ID
columns.description: This item holds the originating temporary transaction�ID for this transaction. If the transaction is a charge, then the originating temporary transaction�ID will be the temporary transaction ID of the charge. If transaction is a payment, then the originating temporary transaction ID will be the payment temporary transaction ID unless the payment is from fast payment. In the fast payment case, the originating temporary transaction ID will be the charge temporary transaction ID.

columns.name: SOURCE_TAR_ID
columns.description: This item holds the source temporary transaction ID for this transaction.  The source temporary transaction ID will always be equal to the temporary transaction ID that generates the transaction.

columns.name: SRC_TAR_CHG_LINE
columns.description: Indicates the temporary transaction charge line this transaction originated from.

columns.name: PAT_AGING_DATE
columns.description: Aging date used for self-pay aged A/R

columns.name: INS_AGING_DATE
columns.description: Aging date used for insurance aged A/R

columns.name: HOSP_ACCT_ID
columns.description: This item stores the hospital account record ID for the transaction.

columns.name: ORDER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the order record that triggered this transaction. This item is not always populated if you use the Charge Router.

columns.name: REFERENCE_NUM
columns.description: This item stores the reference number (check number) for a payment transaction.

columns.name: PMT_RECEIPT_NUM
columns.description: This item stores the receipt number for a payment transaction.

columns.name: REFERRAL_PROV_ID
columns.description: This stores this transaction's referral provider.  Note that this field is linked to the referral source master file and not the provider master file.

columns.name: REFERRAL_PROV_ID_REFERRING_PROV_NAM
columns.description: The name of the referral source.

columns.name: INSURANCE_AMT_PAID
columns.description: This item stores the insurance amount that has been paid on a charge transaction.

columns.name: WRITEOFF_EXCEPT_C_NAME
columns.description: The Yes-No write-off category number for a charge transaction. The value indicates whether the charge transaction was adjudicated as a write-off in charge entry and thus the insurance portion write-off is suppressed.

columns.name: ORIG_PRICE
columns.description: This item stores the original price of the transaction if the price was changed during charge entry.

columns.name: COVERAGE_PLAN_ID
columns.description: The Plan (EPP) ID that is associated with this transaction.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_AMT_COPAY
columns.description: This item stores the original copay amount for the transaction.

columns.name: BAD_DEBT_CHG_YN
columns.description: Indicates whether the charges is written off to bad debt.

columns.name: FIRST_SELFPAY_DATE
columns.description: This items stores the date when a charge first goes to self-pay.

columns.name: CLAIM_ID
columns.description: The claim record for the transaction.

columns.name: EOB_UPDATED_DT
columns.description: Date in which the Explanation of�Benefits for this transaction was last updated.

columns.name: START_TIME
columns.description: Start time of a timed procedure.

columns.name: SERVICE_TIME
columns.description: Time when service is performed.

columns.name: TYPE_OF_SERVICE_C_NAME
columns.description: The type of service category number associated with the transaction.
entries: Ambulatory Surgical Center (Facility usage for Surgical Services)
Lump Sum Purchase of DME, Prostethics, Orthotics
Surgical Dressings or Other Medical Supplies

columns.name: DX_PRIM_CODESET_C_NAME
columns.description: This item stores the primary diagnosis codeset for the transaction.

columns.name: DX_ALT_CODESET_C_NAME
columns.description: This item stores the alternate diagnosis codeset for the transaction.

columns.name: START_DATE
columns.description: The date on which a service is started.

merged.name: ARPB_TRANSACTIONS3
merged.description: This table contains information about professional billing transactions.

merged.name: ARPB_TX_MODERATE
merged.description: Transaction Information that is used moderately often.
